{"url": "http://www.philly.com/philly/health/kratom-opioid-fda-cdc-herbal-coffee-20180320.html", "text": "He contended that kratom does not act on the brain's opioid receptors the way prescription painkillers and heroin do. But back in 2016, the Journal of the American Chemical Society reported that kratom indeed works this way. Last month, an FDA study found that 22 of the 25 of the most prevalent compounds in kratom do bind to opioid receptors, and so should be considered an opioid. The study also said most deaths did occur in people who used kratom in addition to other drugs, though in one case, only kratom was detected.", "images": ["https://www.inquirer.com/resizer/fKm4SllKk6mkn6M0rH7ozwenANs=/500x500/left/top/media.inquirer.com/storage/inquirer/covers/inqFrontPage.jpg%3Fd=20191111-13", "https://www.inquirer.com/resizer/aDWpvAfk3kak3qFp6jDaM6JNkXA=/0x10/center/middle/arc-anglerfish-arc2-prod-pmn.s3.amazonaws.com/public/IM4JBIJUAFDX5BACDFFARTVYEA.jpg", "https://www.inquirer.com/resizer/F-N8i3PLND7jI2semtOn2AwLUlE=/150x150/left/top/media.inquirer.com/storage/dailynews/covers/front.jpg%3Fd=20191111-13", "https://www.inquirer.com/resizer/QhsSiv5Pp6R9UYYdEXuIxRWg5vk=/150x150/left/top/media.inquirer.com/storage/inquirer/covers/inqFrontPage.jpg%3Fd=20191111-13", "https://www.inquirer.com/resizer/TfaOBGALyi_FAYqGNq3Ft1DwxeE=/1200x0/center/middle/www.inquirer.com/resizer/i-eLC-GtxVWwBSy9_mmOpKMj57M=/1200x0/center/middle/arc-anglerfish-arc2-prod-pmn.s3.amazonaws.com/public/H4JWJMAT6JEFDNZCQ24OTEURJA.jpg", "https://www.inquirer.com/resizer/iFXaK9exYdQxesIFLrf0ZK3uMW4=/120x120/center/middle/s3.amazonaws.com/arc-authors/pmn/0b113707-af35-4728-a9f5-35408bd118fe.png", "https://www.inquirer.com/resizer/zUuzzqlEcWWpC9ZJ_1LO0KGtn9s=/1400x932/smart/arc-anglerfish-arc2-prod-pmn.s3.amazonaws.com/public/H4JWJMAT6JEFDNZCQ24OTEURJA.jpg", "https://www.inquirer.com/resizer/P0EHv7XwRp9Ip-NEdUO9xOVtfow=/500x500/left/top/media.inquirer.com/storage/dailynews/covers/front.jpg%3Fd=20191111-13